#### 1. Misal Pav\par
**Ingredients:**\par
- 1 cup sprouted moth beans (matki)\par
- 2 onions, finely chopped\par
- 2 tomatoes, finely chopped\par
- 1 potato, boiled and chopped\par
- 1 tsp mustard seeds\par
- 1 tsp cumin seeds\par
- 1/2 tsp turmeric powder\par
- 1 tbsp red chili powder\par
- 1 tsp garam masala\par
- Salt to taste\par
- 2 cups water\par
- 1/2 cup farsan (Indian snack mix)\par
- 4 pav (Indian bread rolls)\par
- 2 tbsp oil\par
- Lemon wedges and chopped coriander for garnish\par
\par
**Instructions:**\par
1. Heat oil in a pan. Add mustard seeds and cumin seeds. Once they splutter, add onions and saut\'e9 until golden brown.\par
2. Add tomatoes and cook until soft.\par
3. Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well.\par
4. Add sprouted moth beans and boiled potatoes. Mix well.\par
5. Add water and bring to a boil. Simmer for 15-20 minutes.\par
6. Serve hot with pav, topped with farsan, chopped coriander, and a squeeze of lemon juice.\par
\par
#### 2. Kanda Poha\par
**Ingredients:**\par
- 2 cups flattened rice (poha)\par
- 1 onion, finely chopped\par
- 1 potato, finely chopped\par
- 1/2 tsp mustard seeds\par
- 1/2 tsp cumin seeds\par
- 1/4 tsp turmeric powder\par
- 1 green chili, finely chopped\par
- Salt to taste\par
- 1 tbsp oil\par
- Lemon juice and chopped coriander for garnish\par
\par
**Instructions:**\par
1. Rinse the poha in water and drain. Set aside.\par
2. Heat oil in a pan. Add mustard seeds and cumin seeds. Once they splutter, add onions and green chili. Saut\'e9 until onions turn translucent.\par
3. Add potatoes and turmeric powder. Cook until potatoes are soft.\par
4. Add the rinsed poha and salt. Mix well and cook for 2-3 minutes.\par
5. Garnish with chopped coriander and a squeeze of lemon juice. Serve hot.\par
\par
#### 3. Sabudana Khichdi\par
**Ingredients:**\par
- 1 cup tapioca pearls (sabudana)\par
- 1/2 cup peanuts, roasted and coarsely ground\par
- 2 potatoes, boiled and chopped\par
- 1 green chili, finely chopped\par
- 1/2 tsp cumin seeds\par
- Salt to taste\par
- 2 tbsp oil\par
- Lemon juice and chopped coriander for garnish\par
\par
**Instructions:**\par
1. Rinse the sabudana in water and drain. Soak for 4-5 hours or overnight.\par
2. Heat oil in a pan. Add cumin seeds and green chili. Saut\'e9 for a minute.\par
3. Add boiled potatoes and cook for 2-3 minutes.\par
4. Add the soaked sabudana, ground peanuts, and salt. Mix well and cook for 5-7 minutes.\par
5. Garnish with chopped coriander and a squeeze of lemon juice. Serve hot.\par
